  "prompt": "How do I get Jimmy Wales to answer my question on Quora?",
  "response": "To increase your chances of getting a response from Jimmy Wales on Quora, here are some strategies you can try:\n\n1. **Follow Him**: Make sure you are following Jimmy Wales on Quora. This way, you'll receive updates on his activity, and he might notice your question.\n\n2. **Ask a Clear, Thoughtful Question**: Frame your question in a clear and engaging way. Make sure it's relevant to his expertise or interests. Consider questions about Wikipedia, online collaboration, or digital knowledge dissemination.\n\n3. **Engage with His Content**: Like and comment on his answers or questions. Engaging with his content might draw his attention to your profile and your questions.\n\n4. **Be Specific**: If your question is specific and insightful, it is more likely to attract his interest. Avoid vague questions that could apply to anyone.\n\n5. **Tag Him**: If Quora allows, tag him in your question to notify him directly. However, use this sparingly to avoid coming off as spammy.\n\n6. **Leverage Quora\u2019s \"Ask\" Feature**: Use the \u201cAsk\u201d feature to direct your question specifically to him if applicable.\n\n7. **Share Insightful Commentary**: If you have knowledge about a topic he might respond to, comment meaningfully in threads he's engaged in. This could lead to him noticing you more.\n\n8. **Be Patient and Persistent**: Understand that he may not answer every question, even if it\u2019s a good one. Don\u2019t be discouraged if he doesn\u2019t respond right away.\n\nRemember, responses from notable figures can be unpredictable, but following these tips can help increase your chances. Good luck!",
